column1:
2346,Student Communications Specialist/Dispatcher (Ongoing pool 2018/2019),8/2/18,6/1/19,1," Job Summary

Job Summary (Purpose):

This position is responsible for operating several support functions associated with flight activities including dispatching, data collection, flight following, and other customer service items as required by the CWU Department of Aviation. Position will coordinate dispatching activities with student employees, flight instructors, and line and maintenance personnel. Facilitate all of the aircraft transfers from one student/instructor to the next. Provides a professional environment for the CWU students/instructors and verifies all flight-related reports and documents to ensure safety.

Job Duties (Essential Functions):
column2: • Provide a high level of customer satisfaction and maintain a department image appropriate to CWU as a leader in Aviation Education
column3: • Provide accurate data for aircraft/Flight Training Dispatcher check in and room assignments to insure proper billing for all flight and FTD transactions daily.
column4: • Track student lab progress reports using Talon Systems ETA cloud based software and issue reports for lab grading purposes
column5:
• Coordinate and debrief pilots on aircraft discrepancies, assure proper documentation, and report to maintenance technicians in an expedient manner

    • Flight Training Dispatching Requirements:
    1. Adheres to the applicable guidelines of CWU Flight     Training when performing all duties.
    2. Identifies ways to integrate process improvements and efficiencies for various job functions.
    3. Dispatch and coordinate with various departments on a routine basis to cover aircraft (i.e. aircraft maintenance, fueling and cleaning).
    4. Assists in maintaining safety in flight operations.
    5. Maintains aircraft supplies and subscriptions.
    6. Assist with the evaluation of the weather for departure/arrival flights to determine trip feasibility.
    7. Provides the highest level of service and safety for all students and instructors.
    8. Maintains current and accurate information on the Flight Status & Information board.
    9. Provides coordination of aircraft malfunctions and/or inspections between flight crew and maintenance.
    10. Completes fleet efficiency tracking forms and reports on time.
    11. Monitors telephone system and provides prompt response to issues.
    Other duties as assigned

    Required Qualifications (Skills Needed):
column6: • Demonstrated working knowledge of Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) regulations related to flight school operations
column7: • Knowledge of all aspects flight operations
column8: • Knowledge of air traffic control terminology and procedures
column9: • Knowledge of proper radio voice procedures
column10: • Experience and/or training that demonstrates the ability to use Word, Excel, e-mail, database management and internet and/or similar software applications
column12: • Excellent interpersonal and organizational skills
column13: • Attention to detail and strong time management skills
column14: • Ability to implement and follow a general emergency plan
column15: • Ability to read, understand and explain current weather reports, forecasts, and aircraft performance charts
column16: • Ability to express oneself clearly and concisely in written and spoken English
column17: • Ability to understand verbal and written instructions to facilitate the decision-making process and safety
column18: • Ability to communicate effectively with Flight Training students, management and staff
column19:
• Ability to plan and prioritize work efficiently

    • Preferred Skills:
column20: • Dispatching experience with 14CFR 141 flight school operations
column21: • Dispatching experience with 14CFR 121, 135 or Military flight operations
column22: • Experience using Talon ETA cloud based flight school tracking software
column23:
• Collegiate flight school program operations experience

    • Educational Benefits:
    This experience can be translated into many administrative and/or industry applicable experience for future careers.

2423,Student UI/UX and Web Services Intern- Career Services,9/5/18,11/30/18,1," Job Summary

(Purpose):

The Career Services - UI/UX and WebServices Intern would work with the career services team to support efforts to improve and modernize the department’s online and digital presence. This role would be focused primarily in providing web development and UI/UX planning assistance for a variety of department projects and initiatives. This role would also support the department by assisting in exploratory efforts to identify and test digital resources that support student learning, engagement, or career outcomes. In a lesser capacity, this role would also aim to support department communication/social media efforts and assist with other department tasks. This role would entail approximately 30% web development and design, 30% UI/UX testing/planning, 20% office technology management, and 20% marketing and communications.

2254,Student Chemistry Drop-In Help Center Tutor (ongoing pool 2018/2019),6/11/18,5/31/19,1," Job Summary

(Purpose) To ensure a positive and competent learning environment for undergraduates during tutor hours that support learning goals provided by instructors of general and organic chemistry lectures.

(Educational Benefits) Tutors will offer chemistry concepts and problem solving skills to general and organic chemistry students. Best practices of teaching effectiveness will be offered to the tutors by a seasoned faculty member in a one-hour weekly tutor preparation meeting. Tutors will be a part of a team and will, therefore, learn skills necessary for working as a member of a team.



Minimum Qualifications

(Skills) Preference will be given to junior and senior Chemistry Majors with a 3.0 GPA or higher. Students who apply must have at least completed the general chemistry series (lecture and lab) and at least two quarters of organic (lecture and lab).

Undergraduate transfer students must have completed at least one academic quarter at CWU, including chemistry coursework, before they can apply.

Tutors must have strong communication skills and a desire to teach effectively. Punctuality, reliability, and the ability to follow through on instructions are also necessary.
